                " efficiency (5%), the number of incident LCS",
                " gamma-rays (3%), and the electron beam size effect",
                " (< 4.2%)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cross sections of the 139La(g,n) and 141Pr(g,n)",
                " reactions were measured using quasi-monochromatic",
                " gamma-ray beams from laser Compton scattering.",
                "No evidence for sufficient thermonuclear p-process",
                " contribution to the rare odd-odd nuclide 138La was",
                " found."
              ]
            }
